<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-046-095 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 501 056</DOCID><JOURNAL>Industrial Engineering  Oct 1991 v23 n10 p28(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Data collection system improves shop floor tracking. (Hugo BoscaCompany Inc.'s data collection system)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Hugo Bosca Company Inc implements an automatic data collectionsystem manufactured by Monarch Marking Systems Inc to track theproduction of leather goods on the factory floor.andP;  As each itemproceeds through various manufacturing stages, data is recorded onterminals with light bar code wands.andP;  Data is fed from networkedterminals to an IBM PC-compatible microcomputer that updates theinformation for each item being produced.andP;  The company is able tomonitor location and operating detail for all jobs in process.andO;The system also enables the company to keep track of materialsorders and delivery schedules.andP;  The system can generate storagelocation reports, department reports, parts/style reports andexception reports that deal with unaccounted-for jobs, as well asseveral others.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Hugo Bosca Company Inc. (Communication systems)Monarch Marking Systems Inc. (Products).andO;Topic:     Data CollectionAutomationCase Study.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>